who'd been sexually abused by Jackson.

2085
02:09:56.049 --> 02:09:58.760
I have to say. Chris Tucker and Macaulay Culkin

2086
02:09:58.844 --> 02:10:02.180
will always go down in my book
as loyal. good friends.

2087
02:10:02.639 --> 02:10:06.642
They had managers and agents and lawyers
who didn't want them to get involved.

2088
02:10:06.727 --> 02:10:10.313
and they both told me that. "When Michael
needs us. we're gonna be there."

2089
02:10:10.397 --> 02:10:11.522
There were other witnesses.

2090
02:10:11.648 --> 02:10:15.151
people he knew at Neverland.
who came in to tell the truth.

2091
02:10:15.235 --> 02:10:18.529
We had a lot of people that rose to his defence.

2092
02:10:18.697 --> 02:10:22.366
I stood by him
because he was a decent. good man.

2093
02:10:23.827 --> 02:10:26.370
with a warm heart. a loving heart.

2094
02:10:32.544 --> 02:10:35.922
The family were extremely supportive
of Michael Jackson throughout this trial.

2095
02:10:36.048 --> 02:10:37.757
His mother never missed one day.

2096
02:10:37.883 --> 02:10:41.552
The trial lasted almost five months.
She never missed a day.

2097
02:10:41.678 --> 02:10:44.013
I knew what Michael was going through

2098
02:10:44.431 --> 02:10:47.433
and my heart just bled for him all the time.

2099
02:10:48.727 --> 02:10:50.228
The family was there

2100
02:10:50.354 --> 02:10:54.273
and there was this. sort of.
sense that it was gonna be okay.

2101
02:10:57.444 --> 02:11:00.530
I remember they showed
the Martin Bashir documentary.

2102
02:11:00.614 --> 02:11:02.907
and Michael's music was playing throughout it.

2103
02:11:03.075 --> 02:11:04.659
and I remember looking around the courtroom

2104
02:11:04.743 --> 02:11:08.162
and seeing all these heads
bobbing up and down to Michael's music.

2105
02:11:08.247 --> 02:11:09.455
And I thought to myself.

2106
02:11:09.581 --> 02:11:11.541
"Wow. this is gonna be
some crazy molestation trial.

2107
02:11:11.625 --> 02:11:15.753
"because everybody here
is. sort of. rocking out to Billie Jean. "

2108
02:11:16.213 --> 02:11:17.964
It just seemed very surreal to me.

2109
02:11:18.757 --> 02:11:21.843
The prosecution. in my opinion.
didn't know what to do

2110
02:11:21.927 --> 02:11:26.848
with the fact that they found
10 years' worth of magazines.

2111
02:11:26.932 --> 02:11:31.269
Playboy. Penthouse. Hustler. at Neverland.

2112
02:11:31.395 --> 02:11:35.064
which would suggest
that Michael Jackson was heterosexual.

2113
02:11:35.148 --> 02:11:38.776
and interested in seeing pictures
of beautiful women who were naked.

2114
02:11:38.944 --> 02:11:43.406
They weren't quite sure how to fit that
into their theory that he was a paedophile.

2115
02:11:43.490 --> 02:11:47.994
So they came up with the notion that
a paedophile will take magazines like this

2116
02:11:48.120 --> 02:11:50.746
to somehow groom the alleged victim.

2117
02:11:50.998 --> 02:11:53.541
The district attorney showed so much pornography

2118
02:11:53.625 --> 02:11:58.880
that your head was spinning
by the time this was over.

2119
02:11:58.964 --> 02:12:00.631
It was the only day that Katherine

2120
02:12:00.757 --> 02:12:03.968
excused herself from the courtroom
for the afternoon.

2121
02:12:04.303 --> 02:12:08.139
I thought. they're constantly
flashing this material at the jury.

2122
02:12:08.265 --> 02:12:11.809
which was a majority of females. by the way.

2123
02:12:11.935 --> 02:12:15.021
I thought just was stupid.
but that's what they did.

2124
02:12:15.147 --> 02:12:18.441
They couldn't find any pornography
on his computers.

2125
02:12:18.525 --> 02:12:21.485
They had the FBI test
every computer at Neverland.

2126
02:12:21.612 --> 02:12:24.238
they couldn't find any kiddie pornography.

2127
02:12:24.323 --> 02:12:26.657
So they just tried
to fit everything into their theory

2128
02:12:26.783 --> 02:12:28.492
and it just became an absurdity.

2129
02:12:28.660 --> 02:12:33.122
You just knew that there was
really something devious going on.

2130
02:12:34.833 --> 02:12:38.169
This guy. Tom Sneddon.
was really out to get him.

2131
02:12:38.837 --> 02:12:40.755
It had to be totally torture.

2132
02:12:40.839 --> 02:12:44.675
I couldn't imagine what was going on
in his mind and in his head.

2133
02:12:46.678 --> 02:12:48.179
He's not strong in that way. though.

2134
02:12:49.723 --> 02:12:53.643
The stress and strain
of this five-month trial took a toll on him.

2135
02:12:53.727 --> 02:12:57.313
You saw him losing weight.
he was having trouble sleeping.

2136
02:12:57.481 --> 02:13:00.149
I would talk to him at 3:00. 4:00. 5:00
in the morning.

2137
02:13:00.233 --> 02:13:01.484
and he would be terrified.

2138
02:13:01.568 --> 02:13:03.819
particularly about what might happen
to his children.

2139
02:13:04.071 --> 02:13:07.531
He did need some things
to help him fall asleep at night.

2140
02:13:07.658 --> 02:13:12.370
because there was no way he was sleeping
with all this stuff going on in his head.

2141
02:13:12.704 --> 02:13:14.914
I don't know how anyone could sleep.

2142
02:13:16.500 --> 02:13:19.251
The thought that you might be found guilty

2143
02:13:19.378 --> 02:13:22.922
and spend the rest of your life in a jail cell

2144
02:13:23.090 --> 02:13:26.550
and all your accomplishments
washed down the drain.

2145
02:13:27.719 --> 02:13:29.804
I don't know how he coped.

2146
02:13:29.888 --> 02:13:32.223
Most people would've taken a gun to their head.

2147
02:13:32.432 --> 02:13:35.768
His frame of mind was very. very fragile.

2148
02:13:36.603 --> 02:13:38.896
and I was concerned for him.

2149
02:13:39.064 --> 02:13:42.483
He was very worried
about his children and his mother

2150
02:13:42.567 --> 02:13:44.485
and what people would think.

2151
02:13:44.569 --> 02:13:46.237
The first day of Gavin's testimony.

2152
02:13:46.363 --> 02:13:48.280
Michael shows up and he's in pyjamas.

2153
02:13:48.407 --> 02:13:50.700
and he looked like he was in really bad shape.

2154
02:13:50.784 --> 02:13:53.911
And they actually. they had to. like.
help him into the courtroom.

2155
02:13:54.037 --> 02:13:57.581
From that moment on.
everything started to get really awful.

2156
02:13:57.874 --> 02:14:02.086
You started seeing Michael coming
in every day. looking like death.

2157
02:14:02.295 --> 02:14:06.257
It was as if the testimony
was just destroying him.

2158
02:14:06.466 --> 02:14:10.928
To sit there in court
and watch the legal system hurl

2159
02:14:11.054 --> 02:14:17.601
absurd and vindictive and nasty.
mean-spirited allegations at him like this.

2160
02:14:18.437 --> 02:14:20.354
absolutely traumatized him.

2161
02:14:20.605 --> 02:14:24.025
For me. and for other people
who actually knew Michael.

2162
02:14:24.109 --> 02:14:27.319
this was a real human being.
whose life was being destroyed.

2163
02:14:27.446 --> 02:14:29.488
and every day it just seemed to get worse.

2164
02:14:31.616 --> 02:14:35.786
5 months after the trial began the attorneys
presented their closing arguments.

2165
02:14:41.209 --> 02:14:46.005
On June 13th. 2005 after 9 days
of deliberation the jury reached a verdict.

2166
02:14:50.469 --> 02:14:55.306
If found guilty of all 10 charges Michael faced
spending the rest of his life in prison.

2167
02:15:06.860 --> 02:15:12.239
One of the sheriffs came to me and said.
"You've got the best seat in the house."

2168
02:15:12.574 --> 02:15:16.744
And I said. "Why?" And he said.
"Because you're sitting right behind Michael.

2169
02:15:16.828 --> 02:15:18.704
"And when we find him guilty.

2170
02:15:18.830 --> 02:15:23.417
"we're going to get him out of there so fast
that your head's gonna spin."

2171
02:15:23.710 --> 02:15:27.004
These people had already decided
that Michael was guilty.

2172
02:15:27.089 --> 02:15:28.214
And they were sure of it.

2173
02:15:28.340 --> 02:15:31.050
so sure that they had an exit plan
to get him out of there.

2174
02:15:37.849 --> 02:15:42.353
Michael came into the courtroom
and he looked like he was on serious drugs.

2175
02:15:42.771 --> 02:15:48.526
He really. truly looked like a dead man walking.

2176
02:15:51.279 --> 02:15:52.738
It was a tense moment. you know.

2177
02:15:52.864 --> 02:15:55.908
the entire world stopped
to watch what was gonna happen

2178
02:15:56.034 --> 02:16:00.371
to the best known celebrity.
a musical genius. Michael Jackson.

2179
02:16:00.455 --> 02:16:05.251
That was such an awfully emotional day.
you just didn't know what to expect.

2180
02:16:18.306 --> 02:16:20.391
We. the jury. in the above entitled case.

2181
02:16:20.475 --> 02:16:24.061
find the defendant not guilty of conspiracy.

2182
02:16:24.146 --> 02:16:26.897
as charged in count one of the indictment.

2183
02:16:29.734 --> 02:16:34.947
The verdict was read and it was. "Not guilty.
Not guilty. Not guilty. Not guilty."

2184
02:16:35.073 --> 02:16:37.741
All the way down the line.
all counts. "Not guilty."

2185
02:16:37.909 --> 02:16:44.790
And I remember. very specifically.
Michael seeming to not understand.

2186
02:16:44.958 --> 02:16:50.129
And I remember Tom Sneddon looking
at Michael for a reaction

2187
02:16:50.255 --> 02:16:51.505
and not really getting one.

2188
02:16:51.840 --> 02:16:55.301
And I also remember
Tom Mesereau. his lawyer. leaning in

2189
02:16:55.427 --> 02:16:59.513
and mouthing to Michael Jackson.
"You're a free man."

2190
02:16:59.598 --> 02:17:02.433
I could read his lips."cause I was so close.

2191
02:17:02.767 --> 02:17:05.144
And Michael still didn't get it.

2192
02:17:06.771 --> 02:17:08.522
You felt like it was a triumphant moment

2193
02:17:08.607 --> 02:17:12.359
but then when you looked at him.
you realised that he wasn't there for it.

2194
02:17:12.611 --> 02:17:14.445
There was nothing you could do.

2195
02:17:14.613 --> 02:17:17.281
He was so devastated that it had happened

2196
02:17:18.116 --> 02:17:22.494
that you couldn't even find a place
to be happy that it ended the way it did

2197
02:17:22.579 --> 02:17:26.081
because it was so devastating
that it had occurred at all.

2198
02:17:31.796 --> 02:17:36.383
It's sad because I really feel that trial

2199
02:17:36.468 --> 02:17:40.429
is what really depressed
my brother out to the point

2200
02:17:40.513 --> 02:17:43.307
where he just wasn't happy.

2201
02:17:43.391 --> 02:17:46.518
He never went back to Neverland.

2202
02:17:47.437 --> 02:17:49.897
For Michael not to go to Neverland.

2203
02:17:49.981 --> 02:17:51.065
he must've been pretty sad.

2204
02:17:51.149 --> 02:17:55.110
Didn't wanna have nothing
to do with that place ever again.

2205
02:18:00.158 --> 02:18:01.867
He would always tell me.

2206
02:18:01.952 --> 02:18:04.453
"It's over. I don't trust anyone.

2207
02:18:05.038 --> 02:18:09.124
"I don't know why they're doing this to me.
They want me dead."

2208
02:18:09.709 --> 02:18:12.962
He said.
"They're gonna kill me for what I got."

2209
02:18:24.808 --> 02:18:28.727
I'm pretty sure there was times
when he felt that. you know.

2210
02:18:28.812 --> 02:18:33.816
"I wish I was someone else."
or. other than an entertainer.

2211
02:18:35.151 --> 02:18:38.112
There's a certain point
that you can get to with success

2212
02:18:38.196 --> 02:18:39.238
Smokey Robinson
ARTIST. MOTOWN RECORDS

2213
02:18:39.322 --> 02:18:42.283
where you have no life whatsoever.

2214
02:18:43.535 --> 02:18:47.371
You lose the ability to be a person.

2215
02:18:47.789 --> 02:18:50.541
To be a person that cannot be a part
of the everyday life of this world.

2216
02:18:50.625 --> 02:18:52.042
Russell Thompkins. Jr.
LEAD SINGER."THE STYLISTICS"

2217
02:18:53.837 --> 02:18:56.380
it could really be devastating on the mind.

2218
02:18:58.091 --> 02:18:59.925
You can't get it all for free.

2219
02:19:00.677 --> 02:19:02.970
And that's what happened with Michael.

2220
02:19:03.054 --> 02:19:04.179
Freda Payne
SINGER

2221
02:19:04.264 --> 02:19:06.223
he had to give up so much
that he lost his ability

2222
02:19:06.308 --> 02:19:09.143
to just walk amongst everyday people.

2223
02:19:09.561 --> 02:19:12.187
This was the first artist
that I'd been associated with.

2224
02:19:12.272 --> 02:19:13.314
Kenny Gamble & Leon Huff

2225
02:19:13.398 --> 02:19:14.690
PRODUCERS & SONGWRITERS.
PHILADELPHIA INT. RECORDS

2226
02:19:14.774 --> 02:19:16.066
and the only artist
that I'd been associated with.

2227
02:19:16.151 --> 02:19:18.527
that you could not walk down the street with.

2228
02:19:19.654 --> 02:19:24.616
Look at my life. It's somewhat normal.
It's not normal. but it's a little normal.

2229
02:19:25.160 --> 02:19:30.372
But judging my life to his.
his was nowhere close.

2230
02:19:30.874 --> 02:19:33.167
He just couldn't be anonymous.

2231
02:19:33.251 --> 02:19:34.335
Impossible.

2232
02:19:48.683 --> 02:19:51.352
Michael Jackson is proclaimed
the King of Pop.

2233
02:19:51.436 --> 02:19:52.478
Martha Reeves
ARTIST. MOTOWN RECORDS

2234
02:19:52.562 --> 02:19:54.396
It's kind of hard being a king.

2235
02:19:54.481 --> 02:19:56.774
You can get out of sorts.

2236
02:19:58.568 --> 02:20:04.573
I think he. kind of. like. isolated himself
from everyone who would say no.

2237
02:20:06.117 --> 02:20:08.660
Everything he wants is.
"Yes. Okay. Michael."

2238
02:20:09.704 --> 02:20:14.041
It's hard to have someone there

2239
02:20:14.125 --> 02:20:15.376
Billy Davis. Jr.
SINGER. "5th DIMENSION"

2240
02:20:15.460 --> 02:20:18.128
to give you an honest answer. an honest opinion.

2241
02:20:18.213 --> 02:20:20.672
Joseph would always tell him.
"Michael. watch your people.

2242
02:20:20.757 --> 02:20:21.924
"Michael. watch your people."

2243
02:20:22.008 --> 02:20:25.177
He said. "I trust my people.
My people are good people."

2244
02:20:25.303 --> 02:20:28.222
But that's not the case.

2245
02:20:28.306 --> 02:20:29.348
Katherine Jackson
MICHAEL'S MOTHER

2246
02:20:29.432 --> 02:20:31.266
People smile in your face. pat you on the back

2247
02:20:31.351 --> 02:20:33.435
and stab you at the same time.

2248
02:20:33.812 --> 02:20:35.562
These people saw money.

2249
02:20:35.647 --> 02:20:36.772
Bobby Taylor
ARTIST. GORDY & MOTOWN RECORDS

2250
02:20:36.898 --> 02:20:39.066
and they saw somebody who they could get to.

2251
02:20:39.401 --> 02:20:43.070
It was hard for Michael to say no.
as a kid and as an adult.

2252
02:20:45.907 --> 02:20:48.867
Because he generated so much wealth
and so much profit.

2253
02:20:48.952 --> 02:20:50.494
Thomas A. Mesereau. Jr.
JACKSON'S ATTORNEY. 2005 TRIAL

2254
02:20:50.578 --> 02:20:52.996
he became the repeated target
of unsavoury characters.

2255
02:20:53.081 --> 02:20:54.706
many of them mediocre.

2256
02:20:54.791 --> 02:20:58.293
who tried to get near him. promise him the moon

2257
02:20:58.420 --> 02:21:01.672
and then profit themselves by being around him.

2258
02:21:01.756 --> 02:21:05.592
And I think he received some tremendously
bad advice throughout his career

2259
02:21:05.677 --> 02:21:07.052
when it came to finances.

2260
02:21:07.303 --> 02:21:10.639
Michael was an easy touch.

2261
02:21:10.765 --> 02:21:13.559
and anybody could take advantage of him

2262
02:21:13.726 --> 02:21:17.688
just because he trusted everybody's word.

2263
02:21:18.356 --> 02:21:22.067
Michael would bring random people
into his life for business deals.

2264
02:21:22.152 --> 02:21:25.904
They would offer him the world
and Michael would believe them.

2265
02:21:26.865 --> 02:21:30.826
Michael told me he only committed
to 100 shows at the O2 dome

2266
02:21:30.910 --> 02:21:32.453
for his comeback concerts.

2267
02:21:32.662 --> 02:21:35.664
When he found out
that he was committed to 50 shows

2268
02:21:35.748 --> 02:21:38.625
and there was no way of getting out of it.

2269
02:21:38.710 --> 02:21:39.751
he snapped.

2270
02:21:40.044 --> 02:21:44.173
He felt like they'd tricked him.
he was put up against the wall

2271
02:21:44.883 --> 02:21:48.510
and let down by people. or misled. I should say.

2272
02:21:50.513 --> 02:21:54.641
It was thrown on him by his manager

2273
02:21:55.185 --> 02:22:00.397
and. in his state of mind.
he could've said yes to anything.

2274
02:22:00.565 --> 02:22:02.983
After I heard that he was doing
those many shows.

2275
02:22:03.067 --> 02:22:04.485
I started calling him. telling him...

2276
02:22:04.611 --> 02:22:07.279
Then I heard how they were gonna
do them every other day.

2277
02:22:07.363 --> 02:22:11.116
and I told him he couldn't do it that way.
He had to rest.

2278
02:22:11.201 --> 02:22:12.868
And I kept after them.

2279
02:22:16.915 --> 02:22:18.749
The wear and tear

2280
02:22:19.209 --> 02:22:20.918
of all the managers.

2281
02:22:21.336 --> 02:22:24.463
all the promises that they didn't live up to.

2282
02:22:24.631 --> 02:22:26.006
took its toll.

2283
02:22:26.966 --> 02:22:31.553
Probably. a more stronger person
would be able to fight through a lot of that.

2284
02:22:31.638 --> 02:22:33.180
and a lot of them have.

2285
02:22:33.431 --> 02:22:36.642
Frank Sinatra. he was pursued the same way.

2286
02:22:37.018 --> 02:22:39.937
but he seemed to be a person
who could put people at bay.

2287
02:22:40.230 --> 02:22:44.107
But it seemed like Michael has
a certain type of frailty to his self

2288
02:22:44.359 --> 02:22:48.028
and it wouldn't allow him
to be very strong-minded

2289
02:22:48.112 --> 02:22:50.906
or to be forceful with a lot of people.

2290
02:22:51.115 --> 02:22:54.326
Everybody he met.
he trusted them. for some reason.

2291
02:22:55.286 --> 02:23:01.583
And I think that's why Michael
was taken advantage of so much.

2292
02:23:06.089 --> 02:23:08.131
Doctors are human beings. too.

2293
02:23:08.216 --> 02:23:10.092
and they get star-struck.

2294
02:23:10.176 --> 02:23:13.679
and they want a little touch of that fame.

2295
02:23:13.763 --> 02:23:17.849
and they wanna be able to say.
"I'm Michael Jackson's doctor."

2296
02:23:18.893 --> 02:23:21.979
Michael would doctor shop.
like a lot of celebrities do.

2297
02:23:22.063 --> 02:23:24.481
and he'd find the doctor.

2298
02:23:24.607 --> 02:23:28.986
just the right one. who would do the thing
that Michael wanted him to do.

2299
02:23:29.070 --> 02:23:32.656
Michael felt that he needed to escape.

2300
02:23:32.991 --> 02:23:36.493
and he had always been suffering from insomnia.

2301
02:23:36.619 --> 02:23:39.162
from as far back as I can remember.

2302
02:23:39.455 --> 02:23:41.498
Michael Jackson did have a problem.

2303
02:23:41.583 --> 02:23:43.500
Do I believe he was an addict?

2304
02:23:43.626 --> 02:23:46.753
No. I don't believe Michael Jackson
was a drug addict.

2305
02:23:47.589 --> 02:23:49.464
He went through cycles.

2306
02:23:49.924 --> 02:23:54.845
It really depended on what was happening
in his life and in his world.

2307
02:23:55.096 --> 02:23:58.807
I had no reason to think
or believe that he was on drugs

2308
02:23:58.933 --> 02:24:02.019
until my children came to me one time
and they said it.

2309
02:24:02.103 --> 02:24:05.022
and I said.
"Well. I've never seen him in that shape."

2310
02:24:05.106 --> 02:24:08.025
Then I went to him
and ll talked to him about it.

2311
02:24:08.151 --> 02:24:10.152
and he kept denying it.

2312
02:24:13.364 --> 02:24:17.326
I asked him. I said. "Now. Michael.
is there any problems I should know about?"

2313
02:24:18.036 --> 02:24:19.328
"What do you mean?"

2314
02:24:19.454 --> 02:24:23.123
I said. "Well. you know.
once in a while you seem a little dizzy.

2315
02:24:23.207 --> 02:24:24.458
"You wanna go to rehab?"

2316
02:24:24.709 --> 02:24:29.630
"No. No! There you go. See?
Now. why would you assume that?

2317
02:24:29.714 --> 02:24:33.508
"I'm not taking anything. Frank.
I'm not doing one thing."

2318
02:24:34.385 --> 02:24:35.969
One of the people working for him said.

2319
02:24:36.054 --> 02:24:39.389
"You won't ever guess
what this man is doing to get to sleep."

2320
02:24:39.474 --> 02:24:40.557
And ll said. "What?"

2321
02:24:40.642 --> 02:24:42.976
And I was told he's using an anaesthetic.

2322
02:24:43.061 --> 02:24:45.145
And I said. "What?

2323
02:24:45.647 --> 02:24:49.399
"How do you do that?"
I had never heard of such a thing.

2324
02:24:49.567 --> 02:24:54.404
He said. "Dude. I don't know what to tell you.
but that's what's going on."

2325
02:24:54.656 --> 02:25:00.160
Unfortunately. he did find doctors
who were willing to do this crazy thing

2326
02:25:00.244 --> 02:25:02.829
that ultimately led to his death.

2327
02:25:03.873 --> 02:25:06.249
Fire Paramedic 33.
What is the nature of your emergency?

2328
02:25:06.376 --> 02:25:10.212
We have a gentleman here
that needs help. he's not breathing.

2329
02:25:10.588 --> 02:25:13.382
We have breaking news for you tonight.

2330
02:25:14.384 --> 02:25:19.012
the singer Michael Jackson
is reported to have died from a heart attack.

2331
02:25:27.397 --> 02:25:31.108
I heard that my brother had passed away
through my sister Janet.

2332
02:25:31.192 --> 02:25:32.275
Tito Jackson
MICHAEL'S BROTHER

2333
02:25:32.360 --> 02:25:35.612
who asked me to pull over
"cause I was rushing over to my mom's.

2334
02:25:37.198 --> 02:25:38.949
I just couldn't believe it.

2335
02:25:40.451 --> 02:25:45.622
So. I had to just sit in my car
and pull myself together.

2336
02:25:45.915 --> 02:25:47.874
you know. and I went over to my mom's home.

2337
02:25:50.378 --> 02:25:53.296
The entire family had met that evening.

2338
02:25:53.381 --> 02:25:58.552
and was there condoling each other. you know.

2339
02:26:00.972 --> 02:26:02.305
It was rough.

2340
02:26:02.390 --> 02:26:04.808
Just the whole time was a rough time in my life.

2341
02:26:05.560 --> 02:26:08.145
Rebbie Jackson
MICHAEL'S SISTER

2342
02:26:08.229 --> 02:26:11.815
It's so very difficult even to talk about it.
It really is.

2343
02:26:20.241 --> 02:26:21.992
I was heartbroken.

2344
02:26:22.952 --> 02:26:25.328
I was just totally heartbroken.

2345
02:26:26.581 --> 02:26:31.835
It was probably one of the most surreal

2346
02:26:31.919 --> 02:26:32.961
Peabo Bryson
SINGER

2347
02:26:33.129 --> 02:26:39.676
and solemn days of life as we know it.
I would think.

2348
02:26:45.183 --> 02:26:47.642
I was devastated. I started to cry.

2349
02:26:47.727 --> 02:26:48.810
David Gest
MICHAEL'S CLOSE FRIEND

2350
02:26:49.687 --> 02:26:55.984
We had spent 400 years of our lives
as the closest of friends.

2351
02:26:57.320 --> 02:26:59.404
And I couldn't believe it.

2352
02:26:59.822 --> 02:27:02.783
I remember the feeling I got. you know.

2353
02:27:02.867 --> 02:27:04.075
Lamont Dozier
SONGWRITER. HOLLAND-DOZIER-HOLLAND

2354
02:27:04.202 --> 02:27:06.870
It was like somebody punching you
in the stomach.

2355
02:27:07.205 --> 02:27:09.247
God. it was just so...

2356
02:27:17.048 --> 02:27:19.382
I didn't follow the news a lot.

2357
02:27:20.051 --> 02:27:22.385
I'll tell you why I didn't follow the news.

2358
02:27:22.512 --> 02:27:23.512
Eddie Floyd
SINGER & SONGWRITER. STAX RECORDS

2359
02:27:23.596 --> 02:27:29.601
It's because of the people exploiting the man.

2360
02:27:33.940 --> 02:27:35.607
That makes me sad.

2361
02:27:38.277 --> 02:27:40.612
The night that Michael died.

2362
02:27:40.738 --> 02:27:42.948
the next show I did. I mentioned Michael. too.

2363
02:27:43.074 --> 02:27:44.074
Dennis Edwards
LEAD SINGER."THE TEMPTATIONS"

2364
02:27:44.200 --> 02:27:45.951
It just was...

2365
02:27:46.077 --> 02:27:48.328
People just stood up. you know.
They stood up.

2366
02:27:48.412 --> 02:27:51.414
And a lot of people took
their cigarette lighters out

2367
02:27:51.541 --> 02:27:52.916
and just lit it.

2368
02:27:53.292 --> 02:27:56.795
You know. it's just sad. man. It's sad.

2369
02:28:04.720 --> 02:28:06.596
It's just a sad moment.

2370
02:28:06.722 --> 02:28:11.101
to have to carry one of your brothers
to his grave.

2371
02:28:11.769 --> 02:28:16.314
We would perform all night.
tell you the truth. every day.

2372
02:28:16.607 --> 02:28:18.900
It's not a good feeling.

2373
02:28:18.985 --> 02:28:22.112
It's a major part of you died with that.

2374
02:28:24.740 --> 02:28:26.950
And there was this man's house.
who used to sell candy.

2375
02:28:27.076 --> 02:28:31.288
we used to stop there and just load up.
eat candy for days.

2376
02:28:32.915 --> 02:28:34.791
I never lost a child.

2377
02:28:36.752 --> 02:28:41.006
Children are supposed to bury their parents.
not parents bury their children.

2378
02:28:41.632 --> 02:28:44.134
And that's what hurt me the most.

2379
02:28:59.692 --> 02:29:04.487
Many days. I go back to his first cry.

2380
02:29:04.614 --> 02:29:07.782
from the doctor slapping him on his butt.

2381
02:29:07.867 --> 02:29:08.992
up till his death.

2382
02:29:10.369 --> 02:29:11.453
But

2383
02:29:16.667 --> 02:29:22.672
all the memories of Michael are fond to me.
I can't pick out any particular.

2384
02:29:31.182 --> 02:29:33.683
I'm happy with the children here.

2385
02:29:33.851 --> 02:29:37.687
and at the same time.
I'm sad because their father's gone.

2386
02:29:38.189 --> 02:29:41.524
They always say.
"Daddy did it this way.

2387
02:29:41.692 --> 02:29:44.861
"Daddy used to do this.
Daddy used to do that."

2388
02:29:46.989 --> 02:29:50.033
Those kids are so proud of their father.

2389
02:29:52.244 --> 02:29:54.204
I can't find words.

2390
02:29:57.875 --> 02:30:00.377
To me. it's just such a loss. too soon.

2391
02:30:00.503 --> 02:30:01.711
Eddie Holland
SONGWRITER. HOLLAND-DOZIER-HOLLAND

2392
02:30:04.173 --> 02:30:05.548
It left such a gap
and made us see what was missing.

2393
02:30:05.675 --> 02:30:06.675
Valerie Simpson & Nickolas Ashford

2394
02:30:06.759 --> 02:30:07.801
SINGERS & SONGWRITERS.
"ASHFORD & SIMPSON"

2395
02:30:07.885 --> 02:30:10.303
Why hadn't we embraced him?
Why hadn't we loved him?

2396
02:30:10.388 --> 02:30:13.056
He gave us so much love

2397
02:30:13.849 --> 02:30:16.101
and so much wonderful music.

2398
02:30:16.894 --> 02:30:20.397
And I think that this is what
we'll always remember him for.

2399
02:30:23.275 --> 02:30:26.695
I love the fact that everything he sang.
he sang from his heart.

2400
02:30:26.779 --> 02:30:30.740
And I love listening to him singing.
every record he's ever recorded.

2401
02:30:32.284 --> 02:30:37.247
Michael's legacy is that he will be known
as the greatest entertainer ever.

2402
02:30:38.499 --> 02:30:39.666
Michael was a great talent.

2403
02:30:39.750 --> 02:30:42.961
He was the best overall talent
that I've ever seen in my life.

2404
02:30:43.087 --> 02:30:45.255
and I've been following talent
since I was three years old.

2405
02:30:47.258 --> 02:30:48.633
He was the best I ever saw.

2406
02:30:51.429 --> 02:30:55.306
I'll remember that little boy that I met
when he was 10 years old.

2407
02:30:55.433 --> 02:30:56.433
Dionne Warwick
SINGER

2408
02:30:56.517 --> 02:31:02.480
that little feisty. cute.
incredibly talented youngster.

2409
02:31:03.149 --> 02:31:08.945
that went on to become one of the greatest
entertainers that ever lived.

2410
02:31:10.448 --> 02:31:12.115
There's only one Michael Jackson.

2411
02:31:14.952 --> 02:31:17.537
To me and my children.

2412
02:31:17.621 --> 02:31:18.705
Percy Sledge
SINGER

2413
02:31:18.789 --> 02:31:20.457
he meant so much to our lives.

2414
02:31:22.293 --> 02:31:25.795
He was. to me. the greatest entertainer
I had ever seen in my life.

2415
02:31:25.880 --> 02:31:27.130
Whitney Houston
SINGER

2416
02:31:27.214 --> 02:31:30.133
He was a gentleman and he was very kind.

2417
02:31:30.843 --> 02:31:33.303
And I'll always love him. always.

2418
02:31:35.639 --> 02:31:37.766
He was one of the warmest

2419
02:31:37.850 --> 02:31:41.394
and most loveable persons you could ever meet.

2420
02:31:43.814 --> 02:31:47.400
I think Michael's greatest achievement.
throughout his life.

2421
02:31:48.527 --> 02:31:50.612
was making people happy.

2422
02:31:50.696 --> 02:31:52.322
helping people.

2423
02:31:52.406 --> 02:31:57.202
If somebody needed an operation.
or a family starving that needed food.

2424
02:31:57.328 --> 02:32:00.538
he would send over groceries for a year
and things like that.

2425
02:32:00.873 --> 02:32:03.708
I think that's where
he really got his enjoyment.

2426
02:32:03.918 --> 02:32:07.921
seeing somebody sad become happy.

2427
02:32:08.047 --> 02:32:12.258
Those are the things he really wanted
to achieve that was beyond the music.

2428
02:32:13.260 --> 02:32:18.348
We will remember him
as this great showman and humanitarian.

2429
02:32:24.105 --> 02:32:25.271
When people say to me.

2430
02:32:25.356 --> 02:32:27.315
"Do you think of Michael
as being a tragedy?"

2431
02:32:27.399 --> 02:32:29.192
I just don't think of that at all.

2432
02:32:29.276 --> 02:32:32.529
I think that Michael's story is one of triumph.

2433
02:32:33.739 --> 02:32:38.076
This is a man who was the total embodiment
of the American dream.

2434
02:32:38.202 --> 02:32:43.373
This is a guy who came out of Gary. Indiana.
and set the world on fire.

2435
02:32:43.582 --> 02:32:45.375
He did amazing things with his life.

2436
02:32:45.584 --> 02:32:47.293
Did he make mistakes? Yes.

2437
02:32:47.419 --> 02:32:50.964
But that's the humanity of Michael Jackson.
I think. that's most appealing.

2438
02:32:51.382 --> 02:32:53.967
He wanted to make the world a better place.

2439
02:32:54.301 --> 02:32:57.470
That spirit of his is still around now.

2440
02:32:58.055 --> 02:33:03.101
The part that I loved the most about him
was that gentle friend side.

2441
02:33:03.394 --> 02:33:05.812
All the other things. everybody knows about.

2442
02:33:05.980 --> 02:33:08.648
But that part of Michael.
that's the part I love.

2443
02:33:09.233 --> 02:33:10.733
God bless Michael Jackson. you know.
"cause he was one of the greatest.

2444
02:33:10.901 --> 02:33:11.901
Kenny Gamble & Leon Huff

2445
02:33:11.986 --> 02:33:14.486
PRODUCERS & SONGWRITERS.
PHILADELPHIA INT. RECORDS

2446
02:33:15.239 --> 02:33:20.827
Michael Jackson became
the biggest pop star of all time

2447
02:33:21.745 --> 02:33:24.747
but that's not how I'm gonna remember him.

2448
02:33:24.915 --> 02:33:28.168
because he was just one great human being.

2449
02:33:29.962 --> 02:33:33.089
Rest well. my friend. I love you. M.

2450
02:33:34.425 --> 02:33:39.929
Katherine. how do you feel
Michael Jackson will be remembered?

2451
02:33:41.098 --> 02:33:45.935
Well. David. Michael practised one thing.
and it was from his heart.

2452
02:33:46.770 --> 02:33:48.938
L-O-V-E. love.

2453
02:33:49.815 --> 02:33:54.152
And I think he will be remembered
for the love that he had for the world.

2454
02:33:54.278 --> 02:33:55.945
and especially for his fans.

2455
02:33:56.697 --> 02:33:58.448
and his family.

2456
02:33:58.991 --> 02:34:00.658
- Thank you so much.
- Okay.

2457
02:34:00.784 --> 02:34:03.870
- I love you. Can I have a big hug?
- Of course.
